More than 15,000 people have died from coronavirus in UK hospitals, figures from the Department of Health and Social Care show.
The death toll rose by 888 from 14,576 on Friday, taking the total to 15,464 as of 9am on Saturday.
Scotland recorded a further 56 deaths, bringing its total death to 893, according to the Scottish government.
England accounts for 13,918 of the UK death toll, following an increase of 784 since Friday.
In the UK, NHS advice is that anyone with symptoms should stay at home for at least 7 days.